pullRequest.body:
**LinearAlgebra/LinearIndependent**: generalize `linearIndependent_algHom_toLinearMap(')` to allow different domain and codomain of the AlgHom.

**LinearAlgebra/Basic**: add `LinearEquiv.congrLeft` that works for two rings with commuting actions on the codomain.

**LinearAlgebra/FreeModule/Finite/Matrix**: generalize `Module.Free.linearMap`, `Module.Finite.linearMap`, and `FiniteDimensional.finrank_linearMap` to work with two different rings that may be noncommutative. Add `FiniteDimensional.rank_linearMap`, `FiniteDimensional.(fin)rank_linearMap_self`, and `card/cardinal_mk_algHom_le_rank`.

**FieldTheory/Tower**: remove the instance `LinearMap.finite_dimensional''` which becomes redundant; mark `finrank_linear_map'` as deprecated (superseded by `finrank_linearMap_self`.

---

Can you add a primed simpler version without `lift` when things are in the same universe?

I'm not sure that would be useful, because the LHS doesn't have `lift` in it, so you can rewrite in the forward direction without problem and then use `lift_id` to simplify the RHS when M and N are in the same universe. I originally [introduced](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/9677/commits/cc18fb2eda3061f0a1d27e4ad4af1372eae8f17d#diff-6cfabfe01c4ebd977e118300cd5031161533848345f9e5afad4f97795368ebcaR36) a variable M' for the version that you suggest, but later decided to remove it.
I see, good point.

Thanks!
bors r+

By the way, here and in other files there are places where we assume both CommRing and StrongRankCondition because the file doesn't import [commRing_strongRankCondition](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/FreeModule/StrongRankCondition.html#commRing_strongRankCondition) (maybe they predate the formalization of the theorem). Do you think it's a good idea to import Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.FreeModule.StrongRankCondition and remove these redundant StrongRankConditions?
IIRC I made this choice exactly to keep the imports small, but now the import structure changed a lot so maybe it is less reasonable. Anyway a comment is surely a good idea.
I see, added comment.
Actually it was maybe because it created a loop, so we had no choice. Does it work now?

I didn't check this file but I [introduced](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/commit/a3e8d01e04f285df56c4b2a60eaf393b3fceb2ac#diff-1a470a10fd05f0eedb570bfbbe37c36b1a2472e9dc4c78aa7fc070d33ec2c2d2) the import into LinearAlgebra/Dual and it worked.
If it works here I think we can go ahead.
Let me just try it ...
